The paper deals with resource allocation for wireless communication systems, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer networks and communications (cs.NI). The proposed approach uses deep reinforcement learning (deep-RL) and generative adversarial networks (GANs), which are both popular techniques in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also considers constraints on latency and reliability, which are important factors in information theory (cs.IT) and control systems (cs.SY).
